WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.100
Two years ago, I decided to publicly manage an

00:00:03.100 --> 00:00:04.520
experimental investment portfolio

00:00:04.520 --> 00:00:05.900
I named it Hi5

00:00:05.900 --> 00:00:08.980
The Hi5 portfolio started in August 2023

00:00:08.980 --> 00:00:10.780
It began with 500,000 Canadian dollars

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:14.120
After 22 months of continuous investment

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:16.500
plus the effect of market growth

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:17.940
by June of this year

00:00:17.940 --> 00:00:19.300
the portfolio's net value

00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:21.620
has surpassed 1 million Canadian dollars

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:22.720
This important milestone

00:00:22.720 --> 00:00:24.920
The portfolio's compound growth rate

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:26.180
is also close to 12%

00:00:26.220 --> 00:00:28.880
My idea behind the experimental portfolio is simple

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:31.400
I want to prove with a real example that

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:33.260
This is for us ordinary investors

00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:35.400
The easiest way to build wealth

00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:38.240
If you watched my video from two years ago

00:00:39.140 --> 00:00:40.900
but didn't take any action

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:43.880
I think you should seriously reconsider

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:45.560
This asset growth curve

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:47.240
was supposed to be yours

00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:49.900
Achieving this result is actually very simple

00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:51.800
First, keep investing consistently

00:00:51.800 --> 00:00:53.300
Regardless of market ups and downs

00:00:53.300 --> 00:00:54.940
I invest according to plan every month

00:00:54.940 --> 00:00:56.980
I have a clear set of rules

00:00:56.980 --> 00:00:59.840
A fixed amount is invested each month

00:00:59.840 --> 00:01:01.940
Based on how much the market drops

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:03.880
Next, choose the right time to enter

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.560
Then, stick to this set of rules

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:07.580
This set of rules

00:01:07.580 --> 00:01:08.860
Simply put

00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:11.240
is called DCA plus BTD

00:01:11.240 --> 00:01:13.220
I have explained in another video

00:01:13.220 --> 00:01:14.440
in detail

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:16.060
the advantages of this investment method

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:19.160
The DCA plus BTD approach

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.820
allows me to invest more during market downturns

00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:23.800
putting in more capital

00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:26.620
and then during market upswings

00:01:26.620 --> 00:01:27.800
to grow my capital

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:29.620
This investment strategy

00:01:29.620 --> 00:01:31.400
is the key to success

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:34.080
It's about finding stocks that keep rising

00:01:34.660 --> 00:01:36.760
That's why investing in the US stock market

00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.000
is a key part of this strategy

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:42.740
I often see people online discussing

00:01:42.740 --> 00:01:44.440
and they always worry that the US stock market

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:46.120
will crash and never recover

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:47.680
Of course

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:50.040
the main reason might be the media

00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:52.300
which loves to hype up disasters

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:55.260
Creating anxiety is a huge business in itself

00:01:55.260 --> 00:01:56.680
So in my videos

00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:59.800
I aim to help you ease that anxiety

00:01:59.800 --> 00:02:01.300
In the long run

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.660
the US stock market will definitely go up

00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:06.040
This is a rigged game

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:07.800
You could say it is

00:02:07.800 --> 00:02:10.500
because of an oversupply of money

00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:12.340
Or that there's just too much money

00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:14.980
But on a deeper level

00:02:14.980 --> 00:02:18.520
this is the inevitable result of capitalism and vote-driven politics

00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:20.920
Goldman Sachs has statistics showing

00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:23.840
the richest 1% in the U.S

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:26.340
own more than 50% of the stocks

00:02:26.340 --> 00:02:28.740
Meanwhile, the bottom 50%

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:30.620
own just 1% of the stocks

00:02:30.620 --> 00:02:31.600
Think about it

00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:34.600
Who are the ones least wanting the stock market to crash?

00:02:35.460 --> 00:02:37.420
Why are you so worried about a bear market?

00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:40.680
And those who are the wealthiest of the wealthy

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:43.380
confidently put more than 50% of their assets

00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:44.760
into the stock market

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:45.600
So

00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:48.200
if you can clearly understand this issue

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:50.460
investing becomes very simple

00:02:50.460 --> 00:02:51.640
Whenever the stock market drops

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:52.500
corrects

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:55.540
especially when a crash happens every few years

00:02:55.540 --> 00:02:56.760
at times like these

00:02:57.340 --> 00:03:00.600
this is actually an opportunity to accelerate your wealth growth

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:02.840
Because the market will eventually recover

00:03:02.840 --> 00:03:04.300
and ultimately reach new highs

00:03:04.300 --> 00:03:06.880
This is an essential characteristic of the U.S. stock market

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:07.880
But please remember

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:11.200
Here, I am referring to the major U.S. stock market indices

00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:12.580
Some stocks have fallen

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:14.220
They might never recover

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:16.280
Data from JP Morgan shows

00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:19.600
Between 1980 and 2020

00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:23.340
44% of the companies in the Russell 3000 index

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:25.120
experienced catastrophic losses

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:26.720
Catastrophic loss means

00:03:26.720 --> 00:03:30.440
the stock price fell from its peak to its lowest point

00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:31.740
It dropped more than 70%

00:03:31.740 --> 00:03:34.040
And it never recovered

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.460
It never reached a new high again

00:03:35.460 --> 00:03:37.720
In the healthcare sector

00:03:37.720 --> 00:03:40.700
In the technology and consumer discretionary sectors

00:03:40.700 --> 00:03:42.700
Catastrophic losses occurred

00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:44.000
This probability is the highest

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.200
During this period

00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:48.220
42% of the stocks in the Russell 3000 index

00:03:48.220 --> 00:03:50.200
generated negative absolute returns

00:03:50.200 --> 00:03:53.620
66% of the stocks underperformed the market

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:55.380
Only 10% of the stocks

00:03:55.380 --> 00:03:57.700
were able to outperform the market during this period

00:03:57.700 --> 00:04:00.480
And achieved cumulative returns of 500%

00:04:00.620 --> 00:04:01.700
or more

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:04.000
Additionally, in the past 5 years

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.460
the top 20% best-performing stocks

00:04:06.460 --> 00:04:08.220
in the following 10 years

00:04:08.220 --> 00:04:10.040
had a median cumulative return relative to the market of

00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:13.600
Median cumulative return is -17.8%

00:04:13.660 --> 00:04:16.820
Among these stocks, 60%

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:18.260
It underperforms the market

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:19.500
In short

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:22.560
If you hope to grow your wealth by picking a few stocks

00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:24.860
to achieve wealth growth

00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:27.000
statistically speaking

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:28.900
you are very likely to fail

00:04:28.900 --> 00:04:29.740
So

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:32.820
accept that you are an ordinary person

00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:36.120
and invest in index ETFs in the US stock market

00:04:36.120 --> 00:04:39.200
Especially ETFs with a survival-of-the-fittest mechanism

00:04:39.200 --> 00:04:41.760
Consistent, long-term investment

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:44.280
these three points are the easiest ways for ordinary investors

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:46.520
to steadily build wealth

00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:48.020
and also the most effective

00:04:48.020 --> 00:04:51.040
The US stock market's long-term compound return over 100 years

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:52.800
It's roughly around 10%

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:53.840
It doesn't seem high

00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:56.360
But let's look at a set of data

00:04:56.360 --> 00:05:01.080
From December 31, 1992 to September 30, 2022

00:05:01.080 --> 00:05:01.680
During this period

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:03.760
in the U.S. market

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:05.980
among actively managed stock funds

00:05:05.980 --> 00:05:08.960
59% of the funds did not survive

00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:10.480
They either closed down

00:05:10.480 --> 00:05:11.800
or were merged

00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:14.420
30% of the funds survived

00:05:14.420 --> 00:05:17.080
but underperformed the S&amp;P 500 index

00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:19.060
Only 10% of the funds

00:05:19.060 --> 00:05:22.960
survived and outperformed the S&amp;P 500 index

00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:23.580
This shows

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:26.980
A 10% long-term investment return

00:05:26.980 --> 00:05:29.320
is very, very hard to achieve

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:34.500
How to build wealth with around a 10% return

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:36.720
is a question every investor

00:05:36.720 --> 00:05:38.040
must seriously consider

00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:41.160
The more you dismiss this 10% return

00:05:41.160 --> 00:05:42.900
and act overly proud

00:05:42.900 --> 00:05:45.220
the harder it will be for you to build wealth

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:46.760
My Hi5 portfolio

00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:48.920
is like a mirror

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:51.960
Checking it every once in a while

00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:53.060
is beneficial

00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:55.420
The trading rules for this portfolio are very simple

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:57.700
All the trading details are fully transparent

00:05:58.160 --> 00:06:00.060
I believe in what I can achieve

00:06:00.060 --> 00:06:01.200
You can do it too

00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:02.060
Of course

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:03.880
There is no perfect strategy in the world

00:06:03.880 --> 00:06:07.200
The Hi5 portfolio itself also needs to go through natural selection

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:08.820
So the purpose of today's video

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:09.600
is another goal

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:10.740
which is to share with everyone

00:06:10.740 --> 00:06:13.120
the upcoming adjustment plan for this portfolio

00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:15.040
According to the portfolio's trading rules

00:06:15.040 --> 00:06:16.360
in the upcoming August

00:06:16.360 --> 00:06:18.020
when condition 1 is met

00:06:18.020 --> 00:06:19.260
or condition 2 is met

00:06:19.260 --> 00:06:23.280
I will carry out the portfolio's annual rebalancing

00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:25.480
Among the 5 ETFs currently held

00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:28.640
MOAT will be replaced by SPMO

00:06:28.640 --> 00:06:31.420
No changes will be made to the other ETFs for now

00:06:31.420 --> 00:06:32.400
Let me explain here

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:33.820
What does rebalancing mean?

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:36.580
The Hi5 portfolio consists of 5 ETFs

00:06:36.580 --> 00:06:38.660
The initial setup is equal weighting

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:39.560
That means

00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:41.540
the market value of the 5 ETFs is equal

00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:44.780
And every time I add more investment

00:06:45.040 --> 00:06:47.760
I do it based on the equal weighting principle

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:51.160
After running for a year

00:06:51.160 --> 00:06:52.640
some ETFs have risen a lot

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:54.240
while others have risen less

00:06:54.800 --> 00:06:56.080
So I need to

00:06:56.080 --> 00:06:58.960
rebalance the portfolio every year to

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:01.820
bring the 5 ETFs back to equal market value

00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:03.120
This operation

00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:04.340
is called rebalancing

00:07:04.340 --> 00:07:05.620
Specifically

00:07:05.620 --> 00:07:06.700
in August

00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:07.820
when the conditions are met

00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:10.360
I need to take the current portfolio's

00:07:10.360 --> 00:07:11.320
total market value

00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:12.980
add the amount to be invested in August

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:14.380
需要投入的金額

00:07:14.380 --> 00:07:17.360
then divide by five to get

00:07:17.360 --> 00:07:19.800
the market value allocated to each ETF

00:07:20.400 --> 00:07:22.300
ETFs exceeding the allocated market value

00:07:22.300 --> 00:07:23.520
need to have some shares sold

00:07:23.520 --> 00:07:26.580
ETFs below the allocated market value

00:07:26.580 --> 00:07:28.820
need to have some shares bought

00:07:28.820 --> 00:07:29.720
to make up for

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:31.320
let these 5 ETFs

00:07:31.320 --> 00:07:33.880
return to an equal-weighted status

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:36.260
this process is called rebalancing

00:07:36.260 --> 00:07:38.200
the ones to be replaced

00:07:38.200 --> 00:07:40.140
MOAT will be completely sold off

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:43.200
and then SPMO will be purchased

00:07:43.200 --> 00:07:46.800
why replace MOAT with SPMO

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:50.840
SPMO is a momentum model

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:51.520
in short

00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:53.900
it selects from the S&amp;P 500 index

00:07:53.900 --> 00:07:55.600
the best-performing stocks in terms of price

00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:58.140
MOAT tracks the index compiled by Morningstar

00:07:58.140 --> 00:07:59.220
the Wide Moat Index

00:07:59.220 --> 00:08:02.140
it is based on company fundamentals

00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:04.000
A model for stock selection

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:07.080
In the rules for these two ETFs

00:08:07.080 --> 00:08:09.120
there is a survival of the fittest mechanism

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:12.040
Using SPMO to replace MOAT

00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:13.800
logically speaking

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:16.640
it means using the market's survival of the fittest mechanism

00:08:16.640 --> 00:08:20.800
to replace the fundamental survival of the fittest rule

00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.440
Let the market decide who is the best

00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:25.860
From August 2023 until now

00:08:26.620 --> 00:08:28.000
looking at overall performance

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:30.080
SPMO has performed much better than MOAT

00:08:30.080 --> 00:08:32.100
And during the market downturn in March this year

00:08:32.100 --> 00:08:33.440
in the falling market

00:08:33.440 --> 00:08:37.020
MOAT actually dropped before the S&amp;P 500 index did

00:08:37.020 --> 00:08:40.600
The overall drop is about the same as SPMO

00:08:40.600 --> 00:08:42.300
But the recovery process

00:08:42.300 --> 00:08:44.720
But it is far behind SPMO

00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:46.080
From this, it’s clear

00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:48.240
that MOAT’s risk-return ratio

00:08:48.240 --> 00:08:49.980
is not as good as SPMO’s

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:50.740
In other words

00:08:51.220 --> 00:08:53.040
MOAT hasn’t achieved

00:08:53.040 --> 00:08:54.400
the kind of

00:08:54.400 --> 00:08:56.500
defensive goal I expected

00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:57.760
It falls just as much when dropping

00:08:57.760 --> 00:08:59.180
but doesn’t perform well when rising

00:08:59.180 --> 00:08:59.820
So

00:08:59.820 --> 00:09:02.200
in the upcoming adjustment plan

00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:03.860
it will be replaced

00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:07.160
I also hope this adjustment will work

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:10.740
It can properly increase the compound return rate of the Hi5 portfolio

00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:13.720
I want to run it for a while first and see

00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:16.480
If it doesn't meet the expected goals

00:09:16.480 --> 00:09:17.640
then next year

00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:19.620
we will make adjustments again

00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:20.860
In short

00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:22.940
constant adjustments through survival of the fittest

00:09:22.940 --> 00:09:24.720
continuous survival of the fittest

00:09:24.720 --> 00:09:26.980
this is the way to survive in the financial market

00:09:26.980 --> 00:09:27.540
Anyway

00:09:27.540 --> 00:09:29.100
my investment principle is

00:09:29.100 --> 00:09:31.120
to make the easiest money possible

00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:35.080
and to accumulate wealth in the simplest way

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:35.440
Alright

00:09:35.440 --> 00:09:36.220
That's all I have to say

00:09:36.220 --> 00:09:36.800
I'm Lao Lei

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:38.040
See you in the next video

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:38.740
Bye-bye

